<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>KarmaForge</title>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div id="instructions">
        <ul id="get-started">
          <li>Choose your city.</li>
          <li>Find a thing you no longer need.</li>
          <li>See about how much you'd get auctioning on ebay (and if anyone would want it)</li>
        </ul>

  <div id="error-message">
  </div>
  <div id="location" class="form-inline">
    <%= form_for :location do |f| %>
      <%= f.text_field :city, placeholder: "City name", value: @location.city %>
      <%= f.text_field :state, placeholder: "State abbreviation", value: @location.state %>
      <%= f.submit "Next", class: "btn btn-info btn-lg" %>
    <% end %>
    <div class="reset_button"><button class="reset btn btn-warning">Reset</button></div>
  </div>

      <p>Then what? Choose to donate your stuff and forge karma for yourself and your community! Why? Because giving your old things away benefits everyone. And, it's fun! Each item has a karmic value that's revealed and added to your karma points and your city's whenever you choose to donate.</p>

      <p>Want to try to sell it? That's cool. Choose sell and you'll go to ebay's sign up page to try your luck!</p>

      <p>Ready?</p>
      <button id="how-does-it-work">How does it work?</button>
    </div>
    <div id="intro">
      <button id="enter" class="btn-warning btn-lg">Enter the Forge</button>
    </div>
  </div>

    <div id="location" class="form-inline">
      <p>I'm forging karma for: </p>
      <%= form_for :location do |f| %>
        <%= f.text_field :city, placeholder: "City name", value: @location.city %>
        <%= f.text_field :state, placeholder: "State abbreviation", value: @location.state %>
        <%= f.submit "Next", class: "btn btn-info btn-lg" %>
      <% end %>
    </div>

  <div id="ebay-display">
    <button id="donate" class="btn btn-danger">Donate and Forge</button>
    <form id="ebay-button-form" action="http://www.ebay.com" method="get">
      <button id="sell" class="btn btn-primary">Sell</button>
    </form>
    <div class="reset_button"><button class="reset btn btn-warning">Reset</button></div>
  </div>

    <div id="item-search">
       <%= form_for :item do |f| %>
       <p>What do you have? Describe your item as accurately as possible-- some good search terms include: name, brand, material, year, size or condition.  For example, "Shrek DVD 2001"</p>
       <%= f.text_field :name, placeholder: "Enter item description" %>
       <%= f.submit "eBay", class: "btn btn-info btn-lg" %>
       <% end %>
      <div id="item_save_button">
        <button id="item_save" class="btn btn-success btn-lg">Results</button>
      </div>
      <div class="reset_button"><button class="reset btn btn-warning">Reset</button></div>
    </div>

    <div id="ebay-display">
      <p>What does this mean? Here's the average price of the last ten items sold on ebay that match you keywords. And, based on the number of bids on the items, a general idea of the market's interest.</p>
      <button id="donate" class="btn btn-danger">Donate and Forge</button>
      <form id="ebay-button-form" action="http://www.ebay.com" method="get">
        <button id="sell" class="btn btn-primary">Sell</button>
      </form>
    </div>

  <div id="transaction-display">
   <div id="again">
    <button id="forge-again" class="btn btn-warning">Forge again</button>
  </div>
  </div>


    <div id="global-stats" data="<%= stat_data(@locations) %>">
      <h2>Top 5 Locations</h2>
    </div>

</body>
</html>

